.\" Garnet CLI manual page — v4.2 Phase 6A.
.\" Install location: /usr/share/man/man1/garnet.1 (compressed to .gz by
.\"                   the .deb / .rpm build process).
.TH GARNET 1 "April 2026" "garnet 0.4.2" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
garnet \- the Garnet dual-mode language toolchain

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B garnet
.I SUBCOMMAND
.RI [ ARGS ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B garnet
is the command-line driver for the Garnet language platform. Garnet is a dual-mode
language: managed mode (\fIdef\fR + ARC + exceptions) feels Ruby-like; safe mode
(\fI@safe\fR + \fIfn\fR + ownership + Result) feels Rust-like. The mode boundary
auto-bridges errors and ARC-affine semantics.

This binary exposes the full toolchain: parser, interpreter, safe-mode checker
(including the CapCaps call-graph propagator), REPL, code converter for four
source languages, deterministic-build manifest generator, Ed25519 signed-manifest
support, and project scaffolding for three canonical templates.

.SH SUBCOMMANDS

.TP
.B new --template \fINAME\fR \fIDIR\fR
Scaffold a new Garnet project at \fIDIR\fR from the named template. Templates:
\fBcli\fR (minimal CLI), \fBweb-api\fR (HTTP/1.1 service), \fBagent-orchestrator\fR
(Researcher / Synthesizer / Reviewer actors with first-class memory kinds).
Default template is \fBcli\fR.

.TP
.B parse \fIFILE\fR
Parse \fIFILE\fR and print a structural summary of the module.

.TP
.B check \fIFILE\fR
Run the safe-mode checker. Performs syntactic safe-mode restrictions,
annotation-bounds validation, borrow-check skeleton, and the transitive
CapCaps propagator (v3.4.1). Reports violations of \fI@caps(...)\fR coverage.

.TP
.B run \fIFILE\fR
Parse, load, and invoke \fBmain\fR if the module defines one.

.TP
.B test \fR[\fIPROJECT-DIR\fR] \fR[\fB--filter\fR \fISUBSTR\fR] \fR[\fB--no-main\fR]
Discover and run every function whose name starts with \fBtest_\fR in
the project's \fItests/*.garnet\fR files (and \fIsrc/main.garnet\fR
unless \fB--no-main\fR is passed). Mirrors the Cargo \fBcargo test\fR
convention: a test fails iff its body raises an exception.

.TP
.B eval \fI"EXPR"\fR
Evaluate a single Garnet expression and print the result.

.TP
.B repl \fR[\fIFILE\fR]
Interactive REPL. Optionally preload a file before the first prompt.

.TP
.B build \fR[\fB--deterministic\fR] \fR[\fB--sign\fR \fIKEYFILE\fR] \fIFILE\fR
Build \fIFILE\fR. With \fB--deterministic\fR, emit a provenance manifest
alongside the binary at \fIFILE\fB.manifest.json\fR — source hash, AST hash,
prelude hash, target triple, and deterministic flags. With \fB--sign\fR, also
sign the manifest with the Ed25519 key stored at \fIKEYFILE\fR; the
resulting manifest carries a \fIsigner_pubkey\fR and \fIsignature\fR pair
that any consumer can verify via \fBgarnet verify\fR.

.TP
.B verify \fIFILE\fR \fIMANIFEST\fR \fR[\fB--signature\fR]
Verify the on-disk manifest matches a fresh build of \fIFILE\fR. Unsigned
manifests pass hash-only verification; signed manifests always require a
valid Ed25519 signature. Passing \fB--signature\fR makes signature presence
mandatory — an unsigned manifest will then fail.

.TP
.B keygen \fIKEYFILE\fR
Generate a fresh Ed25519 signing keypair. Writes the hex-encoded signing
key to \fIKEYFILE\fR (chmod 0600 on UNIX) and prints the hex public key
to stdout. The public key is what consumers use to recognize the
signer.

.TP
.B convert \fILANG\fR \fIFILE\fR
Convert a source file in \fILANG\fR (one of: rust, ruby, python, go) to
Garnet. Emits four artifacts: the converted .garnet file, a lineage JSON
mapping every emitted AST node back to its source span, a
MIGRATE_TODO.md checklist, and a metrics summary. Output carries
\fI@sandbox\fR by default — human audit lifts the sandbox by changing to
\fI@sandbox(unquarantine)\fR and adding explicit \fI@caps(...)\fR.

.TP
.B version
Print the wordmark + toolchain versions.

.TP
.B help
Print a one-screen usage summary.

.SH CAPABILITY MODEL

Every Garnet function declares its OS-authority budget via \fI@caps(...)\fR.
The v3.4.1 CapCaps call-graph propagator verifies the declaration transitively:
a function that calls \fIfs::read_file\fR (which requires \fBfs\fR) must declare
\fI@caps(fs)\fR, or inherit it via a user-fn caller that does.

Known capabilities: \fBfs\fR (filesystem), \fBnet\fR (outbound sockets, gated
by NetDefaults), \fBnet_internal\fR (lifts NetDefaults' RFC1918 / loopback
denial), \fBtime\fR (clock + sleep), \fBproc\fR (subprocess spawn), \fBffi\fR
(C FFI), and \fB*\fR (wildcard; managed-mode only).

The \fBmain\fR function MUST declare its capabilities explicitly — an empty
\fI@caps()\fR is acceptable for purely-computational programs.

.SH EXAMPLES

Create a new CLI project and run it:

.RS
.nf
garnet new --template cli my_app
cd my_app
garnet run src/main.garnet
.fi
.RE

Build a reproducible, signed release:

.RS
.nf
garnet keygen my.key
garnet build --deterministic --sign my.key src/main.garnet
garnet verify src/main.garnet src/main.garnet.manifest.json --signature
.fi
.RE

Convert a Ruby file to Garnet:

.RS
.nf
garnet convert ruby legacy.rb
# Produces legacy.garnet (with @sandbox header), legacy.garnet.lineage.json,
# legacy.garnet.migrate_todo.md, legacy.garnet.metrics.json
.fi
.RE

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Failure during build or verification.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error (unknown flag, missing argument, malformed subcommand).

.SH FILES
.TP
.I .garnet-cache/
Per-project HMAC'd cache (v3.3 CacheHMAC) storing parse failures, prior
strategies, and knowledge-graph rows. Machine-specific; never commit.

.TP
.I <file>.garnet.manifest.json
Deterministic build manifest emitted by \fBbuild --deterministic\fR.

